The paper deals with the spectral efficiency of wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple antennas and power control is a common technique in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses stochastic geometry to model the spatial distribution of base stations and wireless nodes, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of random matrix theory is also mentioned, which is a topic related to linear algebra (cs.MA). Finally, the paper provides insights into the scaling of wireless networks, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT).
